The NPA says theres lack of evidence against Ephraim Makgoba who is accused of intimidating advocates. JOHANNESBURG The National Prosecuting Authority (NPA) says it has declined to prosecute Limpopos judge president due to a lack of evidence. Judge President Ephraim Makgoba was appointed to the post last year, despite several complaints against him from advocates. Hes been accused of intimidating advocates in cases he presides over, with some calling for a review of Makgobas appointment. NPA spokesperson Mashudu Malabi-Dzhangi says, The NPA has declined to prosecute this matter. There was no evidence, and right now the complainant has launched a civil matter.